
==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[façade#French|façade]]'', from {{It.}} ''[[facciata]]'', a derivation of ''[[faccia]]'', front, from {{L.}} ''[[facies]]'', face; compare '''[[face]]'''

===Alternative spellings===
*[[facade]]

===Noun===
'''façade''' (''plural:'' '''façades''')
# The face of a building, especially the front.
# A [[deceptive]] outward appearance.

====Synonyms====
*(''face of a building''): [[face]], [[front]], [[frontage]]
*(''deceptive outward appearance''): [[appearance]], [[cover]], [[front]], [[guise]], [[pretence]], [[show]]

